# ADR-0004: Adopt Bootstrap (Supersedes ADR-0002)

## Status

accepted

## Context

I have about a week and a half left for my portfolio/site to be completed. With that in mind I need a qicker way to complete what I can before the deadline. This deadline is becomeing the binding constraint, forcing a revisit of the decision.

## Decision

I have decided to use Bootstrap, for the sites styling and layout, superseding the hand-written-CSS decision in ADR-0002.

## Alternatives Considered
The other option was handwriting CSS sheets, as decided in 0002, but with the time constraint, I have to pivot.

The hybrid was another decision, but there may be just too much to manage using two different systems, and it has the chance to introduce too much complexity.

## Consequences

The easier part is that everything will be much faster, and a very large part of the styling will be extremely quick.

The hard part is that I am loosing on CSS learning, and that this could set my learning back a bit since im trying to meet a deadline, and there may be more black boxes that I will have to understand at a later date.